I don't understand why George Lucas edited Star Wars 6 to put young Anakin Skywalker over Darth Vader's original actor. Ruins the message of redemption that no matter what you do in life if you repent and come back to the light it all wasn't for nothing and your life is redeemed.

When the prodigal son returns home he doesn't magically become younger. He has just acquired wisdom by contemplating his misfortunes. Darth Vader's evil years must still be part of who he is. A different example, but Christ still had the Crucifixion wounds after the Resurrection.

Me and my buddy came up with a new crazy kung-fu style gym exercise where we do resistance band assisted chin-ups, but actually loop the band on another nearby pull-up bar, so at the end of every rep you end up with your feet higher above your head and it's mostly a core exercise

I drew a quick scheme of the starting position, you put both your feet in the band and try to end up with your feet as high up in the air as possible on every rep after you clean the bar with your chin so at the top of the rep your body is in a decline horizontal position
